Linux Updates 

Update 

sudo apt-get update 

sudo apt-get upgrade 

sudo apt-get dist-upgrade 

 

Clean 

sudo apt-get autoremove 

sudo apt-get autoclean 

sudo apt-get clean 

 

Fix Broken 

sudo apt-get check 

sudo apt-get -f install 

 

Audit & Configure unpacked but unconfigured packages 

sudo dpkg --audit 

sudo dpkg --configure -a 

 

All of above combined â€“ understand what this does before using it 

sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y && sudo apt-get dist-upgrade -y && sudo apt-get autoremove -y && sudo apt-get autoclean && sudo apt-get clean && sudo dpkg --audit && sudo apt-get check && (sudo dpkg --configure -a || sudo apt-get -f install) 